og_title_final_url: Staff Care | Basic Page | U.S. Agency for International Development
og_description_final_url: USAID is striving for a 21st Century work environment where its total workforce feels valued, and where employee resilience, wellness and work-life balance are integral parts of the USAID culture. USAID's Staff Care Program promotes a range of programs and initiatives that assist with this effort.
USAID partners with countries to fight five neglected tropical diseases (NTDs) that cause illness and lifelong disabilities for more than a billion of the most marginalized people worldwide.
Launched in 2005, the President's Malaria Initiative (PMI) strives to reduce the burden of malaria and help relieve poverty on the African continent.

og_title_final_url: Advancing Protection and Care for Children in Adversity
og_description_final_url: The United States Government envisions a world in which all children thrive within protective, loving families, free from deprivation, violence and danger. Advancing Protection and Care for Children in Adversity: A U.S. Government Strategy for International Assistance outlines the U.S. Government’s whole-of-government commitment and approach to investing in the development, care, dignity, and safety of the world’s most-vulnerable children and their families for the next five years.
